      <div>
        <h1 class="text">Who Dares?</h1>
      </div>

      <div>
        <p class="text">Truth runs deep, where memories dwell—<br>Who said “enough” when so much remained undone?</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <p class="text">The winds carry us beyond thought,<br>confusing us with seeds<br>ready to sprout.</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <p class="text">Sometimes it's useless being a tree that cannot walk,<br>time passes as if unwilling to listen,</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <p class="text">despite the darkness<br>that sometimes never leaves us<br>on this short journey<br>of love's lessons.</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <p class="text">Those who inspire us to grow<br>may be sparrows that won't be caught,<br>or the dawn and a kiss arriving at dusk.</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <p class="text">The path is never clean,<br>no one knows their fate—<br>and those who do, grow fearful<br>and stop choosing for themselves.</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <p class="text">Their harmony disrupted,<br>they can no longer sleep.</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <p class="text">Is it dreadful to think of eternal life,<br>of the transformation of the self?</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <p class="text">Conquering company in parallel lives,<br>in endless equations where time barely exists,<br>and space is the rhythm of a song,</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <p class="text">matched to the speed of our ideas.<br>Life would be glorious with open eyes,<br>and strides long enough to reach places<br>where sunset cannot go.</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <p class="text">The church bell, built in the heart of the desert,<br>is ready to ring—to push us toward the beyond,<br>or perhaps just the here and now—</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <p class="text">painting a snowstorm absent of color,<br>but pierced freely by light, calling us to go further, to the last corner of the universe,</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <p class="text">or maybe only to this verse that refuses to die.</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <p class="text">Free from theory, a lover of action and understanding—<br>it's better to climb your own mountain,<br>and plant your flag at the summit.</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <p class="text">Those who don’t dare build their truth<br>get lost in detours,<br>entangled in themselves,<br>unable to grow in sync.</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <p class="text">I don’t believe in prophets<br>who haven’t lived their faith,</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <p class="text">who, when having coffee,<br>don’t transport themselves,<br>don’t show their courtesy<br>upon seeing a woman—</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <p class="text">don’t savor her body,<br>don’t train their scent<br>to catch that feminine perfume<br>in the half-light—</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <p class="text">a divine appetite where virtue does not exist.</p>
      </div>

